 Day 17 - Pizza With 3N Slices (Dynamic Programming)

## Problem

**LeetCode 1388 - Pizza With 3N Slices**

There is a circular pizza divided into `3n` slices, where each slice has a size represented by an integer array `slices`.

You and your two friends take turns choosing slices:
- You pick any slice.
- Alice picks the slice anticlockwise adjacent to yours.
- Bob picks the slice clockwise adjacent to yours.

This process continues until all slices are taken.

Return the maximum possible sum of the slices you can obtain.

---

## Approaches Covered

1. Recursion
2. Memoization
3. Tabulation
4. Space Optimization

---

## Algorithm

Since the pizza is circular, we cannot take both the first and the last slice.

So we solve two linear DP problems:

1. Include first slice → Exclude last slice
2. Exclude first slice → Include last slice

The final answer is the maximum of both cases.

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | O(2ⁿ) | O(n) |
| Memoization | O(n²) | O(n²) |
| Tabulation | O(n²) | O(n²) |
| Space Optimized | O(n²) | O(n) |

